    "title": "Possession when superior lease ends",
    "explanation": "This ground can be used if the landlord has the property under a superior lease or\ntenancy, rather than owning it outright.\nIf that superior lease or tenancy is ending within 12 months, the landlord can apply to\nthe court for possession using this ground.\nThis ground can only be used if the landlord is one of the following:\n• \ta private registered provider of social housing\n• \tan agricultural landlord\n• \ta provider of supported accommodation\n• \ta company that is at least half owned by a local council",
