    "title": "Possession when superior lease ends",
    "explanation": "This ground can be used if the landlord has the property under a superior lease or\ntenancy, rather than owning it outright.\nIf that lease or tenancy has already ended or will not be renewed, the landlord can\napply to the court for possession using this ground.\nThis ground can only be used if the superior lease or tenancy was originally granted\nfor a fixed term of more than 21 years.",
